Soulful singer, Bukola Elemide aka Aṣa has disclosed why she collaborated with Grammy Award winner Wizkid on her fifth studio album V. Asa made Wizkid’s wish come to reality after she collaborated with him on a unique track entitled, ‘IDG’ (I Don’t Go). The 10-track also features highlife duo, The Cavemen on ‘Good Times’ and ‘All I Ever Wanted’ featuring Ghanaian star, Amaarae. On why she chose to work with Wizkid, she said there was a friendship between her and the ‘Ojuelegba’ singer.   Portable sets to commence road renovation in community     Major changes to expect at 64th GRAMMY Awards     Collaboration with Usher Raymond will be a dream come true-…   “With Wizkid, there’s a friendship. Before the music, we sit down, we have a drink and just talk about all kinds of things— animals and normal things about his life,” she said. Continuing she explained: “I thought it (the song) would be great with Wizkid because it fits his temperament, so I sent it to him and he loved it. It was natural. “Before we do a song, I want it to be honest. We should have a connection with all these collaborators (on the album), that was what we did.” Seven years ago, Wizkid had taken to his Twitter page to express his desire to work with Aṣa.